data.title: Office of the Historian
data.text:
Summary

The United States established a consulate in British Honduras (now Belize) on . Prior to independence Belize had been a British colony since 1862, changing its name to Belize from British Honduras in June 1973.

In the 1960s the United States sought and ultimately failed to mediate a dispute between Belize and Guatemala over contested Belizean territory dating back to an 1859 treaty between Imperial Spain and Great Britain.
